Hehe, I’m really glad you like <a href="http://99designs.com/contests/6774/designers/245307#entry-440085" rel="nofollow">#100</a> Jax… :)

However you’re right about it not being good as a logo.

My favorite is <a href="http://99designs.com/contests/6774/designers/163100#entry-439407" rel="nofollow">#75</a>. The logo integrates the initials SO, draws a stack, and even captures the overflow! Well done.

A technical note about <a href="http://99designs.com/contests/6774/designers/245396#entry-441408" rel="nofollow">144</a>… an infinite for loop does not cause stack overflow. If it had to be code, it could be something like:

void stackoverflow() {
  stackoverflow();
}

but it would suffer from the same problem of not being good as a logo.

Anyway… interesting contest :)
